ğŸ”· Time Complexity â€“ Detailed Explanation

ğŸ’¬ Definition:
        Time complexity tells us how much time an algorithm will take to run as the input size increases.
        
        Iska matlab ye nahi ki exactly 10 sec ya 1 min lagega, balki ye batata hai ki jaise-jaise input badhta hai, time ka behavior kaise badh raha hai.



ğŸ§  Why we use Big-O Notation?
      Big-O ek mathematical way hai performance express karne ka.
      
      Hum always worst-case scenario dekhte hain â€” taaki pata ho ki max time kitna lag sakta hai.



ğŸ“ˆ Most Common Time Complexities
          Complexity	                Name	                     Example Use Case
              O(1)	              Constant Time	              Accessing index of array
              O(log n)	          Logarithmic	                    Binary Search
              O(n)	                Linear	                    Loop over array
              O(n log n)	        Linearithmic	              Merge Sort, Quick Sort (avg)
              O(nÂ²)	                Quadratic	                  Nested loops (Bubble Sort)
              O(2â¿)	              Exponential	                    Recursive Fibonacci
              O(n!)	                Factorial	                Permutations/Backtracking (TSP)



âœ… Examples of Code and Time Complexity

        ğŸŸ¢ O(1) â€“ Constant Time
                    public static int firstElement(arr)
                    {
                          return arr[0];
                    }

                    Even array me 1 crore elements ho, arr[0] ek hi step me milta hai.


        ğŸŸ¡ O(n) â€“ Linear Time

                  public static void printAll(arr){
                      for(int i : arr){
                          System.out.println(i);
                      }
                  }
                  
                  10 elements â†’ 10 steps
                  1 crore elements â†’ 1 crore steps


        ğŸ”´ O(nÂ²) â€“ Quadratic Time
        
                for i in range(n):
                    for j in range(n):
                        print(i, j)
        
                Ek loop O(n), dusra bhi O(n) â†’ Total = O(n Ã— n) = O(nÂ²)


        ğŸ”· O(log n) â€“ Logarithmic Time
      
              # Binary Search
                  low = 0
                  high = n-1
                  while low <= high:
                      mid = (low + high) // 2
                      if arr[mid] == target:
                          return mid
                      elif arr[mid] < target:
                          low = mid + 1
                      else:
                          high = mid - 1

                  Har step me input half ho raha hai â†’ n â†’ n/2 â†’ n/4 â†’ n/8 ... = O(log n)



ğŸ¯ Important Points for Time Complexity:

          Loop â†’ mostly O(n)
          
          Nested loop â†’ O(nÂ²)
          
          Divide & Conquer â†’ O(log n) or O(n log n)
          
          Recursion â†’ Can be anything! (Need dry-run or recurrence relation)



âœ… Step-by-Step Shortcut

          1. Line-by-line check kar
          
          2. Loops dhoondh:
          
                  Loop of n â†’ O(n)
                  
                  Nested loop â†’ Multiply: O(nÂ²)
                  
                  Loop that halves â†’ O(log n)

          
          3. Function calls:
          
                Recursion â†’ check how many times call ho raha hai
          
          
          4. Ignore constants like 2n â†’ O(n), n+100 â†’ O(n)
          
          5. Multiple loops (not nested) â†’ Add: O(n) + O(m) = O(n + m)
          
          6. Conditionals (if/else) â†’ Max one chalega, to take worst-case one


ğŸ§ª Examples:
        âœ… Example 1: Single loop
              
              for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
                  System.out.println(i);
              }

              â± Time Complexity = O(n)


        âœ… Example 2: Nested Loop
        
              for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
                  for(int j = 0; j < n; j++) {
                      System.out.println(i + ", " + j);
                  }
              }

              â± Time Complexity = O(nÂ²)


        âœ… Example 3: Two separate loops

              for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
                  System.out.println(i);
              }
              for(int j = 0; j < m; j++) {
                  System.out.println(j);
              }

              â± Time Complexity = O(n + m)


        âœ… Example 4: Binary Search
        
              while(low <= high) {
                  int mid = (low + high)/2;
                  if(arr[mid] == target) return mid;
                  else if(arr[mid] < target) low = mid + 1;
                  else high = mid - 1;
              }

              â± Time Complexity = O(log n)


        âœ… Example 5: Recursion
                Jab ek function khud ko baar-baar multiple times call karta hai, aur har ek call se 2 aur calls bante hain â€” tab hoti hai O(2^n) complexity.

Ye recursion tree banata hai â€” jisme har level pe number of function calls double ho jaate hain.

                                          fib(4)
                                       /         \
                                   fib(3)       fib(2)
                                  /     \        /     \
                             fib(2)   fib(1)  fib(1)  fib(0)
                             /    \
                         fib(1)  fib(0)


                int fib(int n) {
                    if(n <= 1) return n;
                    return fib(n-1) + fib(n-2);
                }

                â± Time Complexity = O(2^n) â—(because tree recursion)

                  Ab dekh â€” kitne function calls ban rahe hain?
                  
                  â¡ fib(4) â†’ 1 call
                  â¡ fib(3), fib(2) â†’ 2 calls
                  â¡ fib(2), fib(1), fib(1), fib(0) â†’ 4 calls
                  â¡ fib(1), fib(0) â†’ 2 calls
                  
                  Total = 1 + 2 + 4 + 2 = 9 calls
                  
                  Pattern: Har level pe calls double ho rahe hain â‡’ 1, 2, 4, 8, â€¦
                  Thatâ€™s why it's O(2^n)

                â— Kyu Kharab Hai ye?
                            Agar tu fib(40) karega â€” to almost 1 billion calls honge ğŸ˜¨
                            Slow, inefficient, waste of CPU and timeâ€¦



ğŸ”· Space Complexity â€“ Detailed Explanation

ğŸ’¬ Definition:
        Space complexity is the total memory space used by an algorithm including input + auxiliary (extra) space.


âœ… What contributes to space?
        Input space (already given data)
        
        Variables
        
        Recursion stack space
        
        New data structures (arrays, hashmaps)


ğŸ“ˆ Common Space Complexities
              Complexity	          Meaning	                      Example
                O(1)	            Constant space	          No extra storage
                O(n)	            Linear space	            Making new array
                O(nÂ²)	              Matrix	                      2D Array
                O(log n)	        Recursion (Binary)	      Binary Search (recursive)


âœ… Examples:
ğŸŸ¢ O(1) â€“ Constant Space
python
Copy
Edit
def find_sum(arr):
    total = 0
    for i in arr:
        total += i
    return total
Sirf total ek variable banaya â†’ constant space

ğŸŸ¡ O(n) â€“ Linear Space
python
Copy
Edit
def make_copy(arr):
    new_arr = []
    for i in arr:
        new_arr.append(i)
    return new_arr
Har element ke liye ek memory â†’ O(n)

ğŸ”´ O(nÂ²) â€“ 2D Matrix
python
Copy
Edit
arr = [[0]*n for _ in range(n)]
n*n values store ho rahe hain

ğŸ” Recursion & Space
python
Copy
Edit
def factorial(n):
    if n == 0: return 1
    return n * factorial(n-1)
Har call memory stack me jaata hai
Recursive depth = n â†’ O(n) space

âš”ï¸ Time vs Space Trade-Off
Kabhi kabhi hum fast algorithm ke liye zyada memory use karte hain.

Example:

Searching in array â†’ O(n)

Searching in hashmap â†’ O(1) (but memory zyada)

ğŸ§ª Quick Test (Check Yourself):
python
Copy
Edit
# TC? SC?
def double_elements(arr):
    result = []
    for i in arr:
        result.append(2*i)
    return result
âœ”ï¸ Time Complexity â†’ O(n)
âœ”ï¸ Space Complexity â†’ O(n) (new array bana raha hai)

âœ… Summary
Feature	Time Complexity	Space Complexity
Measures	Time taken by algorithm	Memory used by algorithm
Best	O(1)	O(1)
Bad	O(nÂ²), O(2â¿), O(n!)	O(nÂ²), O(n)
Related to	Loops, Recursion, etc.	Variables, Structures
Goal	Fast solution	Less memory used
ğŸ§  Tips:
Loop â†’ time badhta hai

Array/Map bana rahe ho â†’ space badhta hai

Recursion â†’ mostly both time and space heavy

Focus on asymptotic behavior (ignore constants like 2n â†’ O(n))




